The food was fine but the staff was very rude to us. When my cousin and I sat down and talked in English (I am Vietnamese but live in Germany, my cousin is Vietnamese), the staff was looking at us. Then while eating, a man (probably the owner?) asked us where we come from. We told him I was Vietnamese but from Germany and she was Vietnamese. Few minutes later more customers came into the restaurant and the man started speaking English to them, even though they were vietnamese. He started talking to other customers in English too who came before us. We heard that the customers were obviously all Vietnamese..
He was making fun of us by suddenly speaking English eventhough we were Vietnamese nationality. My Vietnamese is broken, so it was more comfortable for me to speak English. He disrespected us in such a bad, rude and disrespectful way..

Will never eat here again. This is racism that I am not going to take. We will go elsewhere for B√°nh Tr√°ng N∆∞·ªõng but not here anymore.

üî•HONG KONG MILK TEA IN ASIA 9K SIZE M - 17K SIZE L SUPER ATTRACTIVE RIGHT IN SON TRA AREA, guys

Hongkongbaley.tea Milk Tea
üßã 131 Pham Van Xao, Son Tra, DN
‚è∞ 9am - 10pm

When mentioning the famous milk tea brand without fat in Saigon, everyone probably thinks of Baley.Tea - a franchised Hong Kong milk tea chain with more than 100 branches across the country.

Here, there are more than 20 types of drinks and more than 10 types of toppings. Famous for its characteristic less sweet and fatty milk tea taste but without the smell of fatty powderüëç. The accompanying topping stands out with soft tapioca pearls or a rich, creamy egg custard that is lightly torched and fragrant with Caramel scent. Strawberry tea and lychee tea are an option for those who like sweetness and favor the smell of tea. You can order anything from just 9k and you'll get a full glass.

‚ú®Currently, the program will take place for 3 days, May 9-10-11. After ending, each glass will range from 15k to 30k depending on the type of tea. So take advantage of the opportunity to tag your child every day to ask for treats quickly.

I was so excited to try this place especially since the reviews raved it! We came in the morning but it was sold out so we came back in the evening.

We got the Char Siu sandwich and it was nothing spectacular. There was no pickled daikon or carrots. The pork...well all u tasted pretty much every bit was just fat pieces. There was mint and cucumber inside as well.

I have had much better Vietnamese Sandwiches so it was quite disappointing.

It was $20,000. Maybe I should have asked for additional meat, or just extra fat pieces? You can see from the pieces, the top pink was the pork skin, the 2nd and 3rd pieces were the fat of the char siu. I was sadly disappointed after reading such high reviews.

The girl was really nice, the atmosphere was cute as well. Just the sandwich wasn't all that was hyped up to be. So sad.

reviews.author: Khoa D∆∞∆°ng
reviews.text:
The buffet experience of 169k/person is really bad:
- The restaurant is very empty, the staff sits around and calls an entire table, but the waiter has to call 2 or 3 times to get there, customers only serve their orders themselves.
- The quality of the food is not bad, but the price of 169k is too expensive, the taste is somewhat rancid, especially the vegetables, mushrooms and shrimp.
- Grilled but actually fried, no charcoal, just a frying pan on a gas stove, so bad that I had to order a stove that only had cooking oil but the food was still so bad I couldn't save it (pig trough)
- The hot pot has 2 compartments but the hot pot water is the same, no difference at all. The hot pot stuffing is fine for temporary use and can be said to be the only thing that can be swallowed during the entire eating process (frozen food is available)
- Dessert, simple appetizers, cold food.
- Soft drinks are like sugar water, not carbonated and have a bland taste
- The atmosphere and tables of the restaurant are very dirty, smelly and oily even before I entered, even though the restaurant had not had a single customer sitting before.

In summary, the restaurant's business is not virtuous. The food experience is worse than eating at street vendors

reviews.author: All Things Oahu
reviews.text:
Was told about this place so we came here to try! We asked for the large combination and asked for extra veggies as we always do everywhere. Prefer less noodles and more veggies.

The broth had a deep flavor of crab and we could taste it! There were several pieces of Rieu but it was mostly meatball and not much crab flavor in the "rieu" but then again, no places makes it with much crab like how I make it at home.

We notice that we are usually still hungry after because there isn't enough protein in Vietnamese portions but was a very nice surprise here at this place. There was quite a bit of meat and proteins in the soup bowl that we were so full at the end and didn't have to eat a snack by time we got home.

We thoroughly enjoyed our meal and will be back!

Staff was friendly as well so we appreciated it.

This vibrant eatery, though small, draws in crowds eager for a bowl of steaming B√∫n Ri√™u. Finding a seat might be a bit of a challenge, as the eatery's popularity often outpaces its available tables. For solo diners, there is a high possibility that you will always have to share the table with friendly strangers.

For VND 30.000, you can enjoy a satisfying portion of Ri√™u Ch·∫£. The bowl arrives laden with chewy pork rolls, their faint cinnamon fragrance tickling the nose. But if you are feeling extra hungry, the VND 50.000 large mixed bowl guarantees to leave you happy and full.

However, be prepared for a bold flavour profile. The broth, undeniably satisfying, leans towards the saltier side, lacking the subtle sweet and sour balance of a Saigon-style b√∫n ri√™u.

I recently visited this cozy cafe, and I was absolutely delighted with its atmosphere! I especially liked the vibe of the green garden - it seems like you are in a real oasis. I found out that they even have a second floor, but, unfortunately, I wasn‚Äôt able to see it because I came here in rainy weather.

The inside of the establishment is also very nice: cozy, clean, and guests are greeted with warmth. Special thanks to the girls who work here, they are lovely. Right after the rain, one of them brought a fan to keep my husband and I cool as we sat outside in the gazebo. Ahh, careüß°

Now about the drinks. The menu is quite varied, but I was sad that there was no matcha latte that I wanted to try. Instead, I ordered coconut coffee, and to be honest, it was more like a dessert: thick white liquid, jelly, not completely ground ice and coconut shavings on top. I may have gotten this result because I asked for it to be made without sugar, but I'm not sure what that has to do with it. But my husband had classic peach tea, and it turned out to be much more successful than my order.

Overall, the establishment left a very pleasant impression, especially thanks to the green area and friendly staffüòå

reviews.author: R Benn
reviews.text:
What I find about famous vietnamese restaurants, is that they are truly family run businesses and the decor is nothing to be desired. What you would easily pass by and not look twice at, has the most amazing food.
Banh Canh Ruong is one of these little hidden gems.
Known for the dish 'Banh Canh Roung', this bowl of exquisite pork, fish and noodles is blended with a small amount of chili and spices along with the famous fish sauce to make a taste that is pure heaven on the tongue. Oh. I forgot to mention the quail eggs also..lovely.
For the two of us we had the main dish along with iced cane juice. That came to only 110k dong.
Very cheap and tasty. The restaurant was full when we left, and testiment to the validity of its reputation.
Well done to the restaurant. 9/10 easily.

reviews.author: Joshua Stubbins
reviews.text: Banh Canh Ruong from this well run restaurant is a delicious. With meat so unbelievably tender and the noodles a wonderful springy texture , a fragrant tangy soup which pairs so well and wonderfull fried rolls that are the perfect texture change in the meal, I would highly recommended this restaurant to any who come to Danang. The service is prompt and the staff friendly

The service in this establishment was like fine dining. The lady ‚Äòem pulled out the chair for me to sit, a waitress came over to my table and laid my utensils on a holder so they don‚Äôt touch the table. Another waitress walks around and puts ice in your drink if it‚Äôs melted. The atmosphere is very pleasing to the eye as well.
I only had a margarita pizza and a coke.
The pizza was ok. It definitely had a ton of cheese on it, which is always a good thing.
I just wasn‚Äôt digging the sauce., The crust as well. Matheus may have better of other I just haven‚Äôt tried.

reviews.author: Brad R
reviews.text: This new restaurant/bar is an undiscovered gem facing the riverfront. It has a beautiful Greek-inspired design, open-air with cool breezes coming off the river, and great views from the 2nd floor. I ordered a pizza and it was the best I‚Äôve had in years. The ingredients taste very fresh and high quality. I experienced a rare feeling of nourishment that words can‚Äôt describe. For cocktail lovers, they have a wide variety of choices. It was so good that I came here again the next morning for breakfast. I tried eggs benedict. Perfectly cooked. The mango peach smoothie was delicious. It‚Äôs obvious that the owner prioritizes ambiance and passion for quality of ingredients. The number of entres is somewhat limited, but clearly the chef focuses on preparing a few dishes very well rather than overcrowding the menu. Attentive, friendly, professional staff. Highly recommended and worth catching a Grab from wherever you‚Äôre staying if you‚Äôre in the mood for top-notch Western food & cocktails that you‚Äôll want to come back for again and again.

reviews.author: Mai Anh
reviews.text: I made a dinner reservation for two people with dishes as shown in the picture. The food was delicious, with European flavors and perfectly seasoned. The staff were friendly and provided excellent service. Although I read some mixed reviews about the food, my meal yesterday was fantastic. And let‚Äôs not forget the impressive architecture ‚Äì a solid 10 out of 10! I highly recommend this place for romantic dinner dates. I‚Äôll definitely be coming back.

reviews.author: RayRayRay Tan
reviews.text:
Certainly intriguing... A colossal building adorned in a Roman or ancient Greek style, standing out as entirely foreign to Da Nang's scenery. It's another Instagram check-in spot offering average coffee and snacks.

On the positive side, the staff is service-oriented, even delivering your drink if you're seated on the second floor. In summary, it's simply a fascinating place to unwind and feel like you've been transported to another planet or universe, perhaps.

reviews.author: Hi·∫øu Ho√†ng Minh
reviews.text:
There is never a time when I come to Da Nang that I don't stop by the restaurant

The local shop run by old aunts has been selling the same for many years, the flavor is always rich and authentic. A cheap bowl costs 20k, a large bowl costs 30k. There are tapioca noodles or rice flour, chewy tapioca noodles, soft rice flour eaten with rolls, tendons, quail eggs or bones. The noodles are soaked in broth so they are very absorbent and rich. 1 hot bowl, add a little chili powder, a little fish sauce, squeeze a few drops of delicious lemon.

The shop has a sign that it opens at 11:30 a.m., but it opens around 10:30 a.m. and sells until sold out. The shop is very small, people sit close together, when someone stands up, someone sits down. You should go early and not leave it until the afternoon. You can order it with fried chicken or pork skin and eat chug, it will be delicious. Every time I eat 2 new bowls

Next door there are delicious and cheap fruit juices sold. After eating 1 bowl of noodles and 1 glass of water, it's great

The sales ladies are also quite welcoming and quick.

reviews.text:
üè† The shop is located at the corner of Han Thuyen street and Nguyen Pham street. The restaurant space is small and popular. The indoor area is used as a kitchen to prepare food, so the restaurant only has outdoor seating (seating on the sidewalk, covered). The shop has low tables and chairs made of bamboo (the chairs do not have backrests, the tables and chairs are not sturdy and easily shake). The restaurant has a few small shared trash cans between tables.

üç± The shop mainly sells Bun Dau Mam Tom, along with snacks such as: Fried Nem Chua, Fried Pork Chop, Grilled Jackfruit Snails, Stuffed Snails,... I tried the Bun Dau Mam Tom, the tofu mold was delicious, Crispy crust, pork here uses pork leg meat. Shrimp sauce is delicious but the bowl of fish sauce is small so when dipping it it is easy to spill the fish sauce out.

üí∞ The restaurant has a menu with clear prices and illustrations for each dish. A portion of Bun Dau (full) is 35k, enough for one person to eat. The price range is acceptable compared to the quality of the food and the space and location of the restaurant.

üåü The restaurant is more suitable for takeout rather than eating at the restaurant. If you eat at the restaurant, you can go individually or in groups of 2-4 people. If there are more people, combine tables. The restaurant has table service, but the number of staff is small so service will be slow if crowded.

üïõ This review was written after visiting the restaurant on January 9, 2024.

reviews.author: Loan Ng
reviews.text:
Ms. My also offers private cooking class of her tantalizing bun bo Hue and I‚Äôm beyond thrilled to have this amazing experience. I was at her restaurant and love the way she crafted the broth; it is clear, restraint, yet flavorful. The private cooking class entails ordering a day ahead meat and bones based on number of servings, and shopping together at the Han Market from a comprehensive list of ingredients. Then we proceed to cook for three hours in the kitchen. There is no short cuts, as she explained that the timing and order to add the ingredients can elevate the broth from good to great. She holds no secrets and pour all her knowledge to share.
While the quality of the meat at the Han Market pales in comparison to beef sourced for her restaurant, we managed to serve the most delicious bowls of bun bo Hue at home. I hope everyone can take advantage of this unique opportunity in Da Nang.

reviews.author: Ritrka

reviews.text:
A very authentic local resto. Pork Roll is the signature dish but we ordered some different dishes for lunch - Quang noodle, fresh spring roll & Cao Lau noodle.

The rice paper of Fresh spring roll was super soft & chewy, the shrimp was fresh and tasted super nice with the sour & chilli sauce!

Noodles were another highlight. Cao Lau noodle is Hoian signature dish which you can hardly find outside Danang & Hoian. The noodle was so al dente and absorbed all the sauce that made it so flavour-able.

reviews.text: Avoid this place at all costs. I went there for dinner, had some m·ª≥ qu·∫£ng (noodles with pork) and a bottle of mineral water. The noodles had no taste at all. They were so bad I couldn't eat half of the bowl. Also, they opened the bottle of water for me, so I couldn't tell if it was already opened and filled with tap water. The next morning I woke up with diarrhea, vomits and fever. I was feeling well during my trip up until the moment I ate here. Maybe they don't storage the food the right way. The fact is I got really sick after I ate here. Also, the guy receiving people had an aggressive attitude, pushing you to get in and order right away, making me sit next to the entrance, where air conditioner couldn't reach. Do yourself a favor and avoid this place.

The food was okay. Nothing too crazy. We ordered the rolls with pork. The server didn‚Äôt even ask us if we know how to roll them or suggest that he shows us. The only good thing was the dipping sauce for the rolls. That‚Äôs it.

Just a disappointing place. Won‚Äôt be coming back here.

reviews.author: Marc SWM
reviews.text: Excellent service. Very warm staff who speak a bit of English. However the food was pretty bad. Very gristly pork and it had a feeling like it wasn't fresh. I'm a huge fan of Central Vietnamese cuisine and love to try new places. But this is very substandard. They were busy and will get plenty of walk in traffic so I'm not worried this will hurt their business but for those who really have a passion for central cuisine give this place a pass unless they improve the quality of their dishes. Even the "tra da" tasted like tap water and wasn't properly prepared (this is the easiest thing to get right in vn!)

This is not a pho restaurant, just in case you were wondering as I was, but a cafe, located directly across from Danang train station. Danang station is pretty unique in my experience, because most stations have nothing remotely enticing (food or drink wise) close by, but this station has multiple coffee shops, bars, a decent com tam restaurant, and even a Korean bbq place.
I‚Äôve frequented this particular cafe on multiple occasions, and the drinks here have always been delicious and very reasonably priced. Whether you just got off a long train ride or are waiting around for your train to arrive, I wholeheartedly recommend grabbing a cafe den da khong dung here!

reviews.text: Although I arrived at the eatery at 6 PM, I was surprisingly their last customer for the day. The rice portion was quite generous, but I would have preferred it to be a bit drier. The kimchi that accompanied the meal lacked a bit of sourness. However, the chicken and ribs were expertly marinated, bursting with rich flavours. The cucumbers were drizzled with a refreshing lime leaf-infused sauce. The owner, with great enthusiasm, introduced their homemade soy sauce, which was a delightful addition to the meal. I highly recommend visiting this eatery, but be sure to arrive around noon for the best experience.

I had the opportunity to enjoy fried chicken at KFC restaurant Nguyen Huu Tho branch and was really impressed by the quality of the food as well as the service attitude of the staff here.
- The KFC fried chicken at this branch that I ate felt like it had a crispy crust, and the meat inside was soft and delicious. Unique flavor
Every time I come here, I don't have to worry about lack of choice because KFC's menu is extremely diverse, not only does it have fried chicken, but it also has many different combos. I like this variety, because you can choose according to your taste.
Even though it is fast food, KFC always serves quickly and attentively. This helps me save time and satisfy my hunger.
Comfortable space: KFC restaurants often have spacious, clean and comfortable spaces. This creates a pleasant feeling when enjoying a meal.
In short, KFC is not just an ordinary fried chicken restaurant, but also a memorable experience. I will rate this restaurant 5 stars and will come back next time

The 30k box of mixed sticky rice is very filling, fragrant pate, and sweet ground chili sauce are two things I really like.
Thai green tea is also fragrant, priced at 10k.
In short, for 40,000 VND for an afternoon meal, it's too stable üòö
Fans of sticky rice should not miss it.

The downside is that the restaurant has few tables and chairs and it's a bit hot to eat in.

reviews.text:
‚ù§Ô∏è I haven't eaten sticky rice vs. bread in a long time - LONG TIME NO BREAD AND STICKY RICE üòÇ
C vs J bread has never been reviewed üòÇ Sticky rice is okay once, but it's not that rare to eat üòó
On a less lazy day, the two of us wandered around the other side of the river to see what we could find for breakfast and found this bread and sticky rice shop. J eats Saigon Mixed Sticky Rice for 25k, and C eats Traditional Bread for 16k üòö Comes with 1 soy milk and 1 squash ginseng tea. The sticky rice is quite filling, but the price is still a bit high compared to other products. All the food stalls look very clean and neat. In general, the ingredients in the sticky rice are delicious, the pate is very fragrant even though there isn't much of it üòä The bread is a bit salty, due to the jam + a lot of water, but it's still quite delicious.
There are many other types of bread and sticky rice here, they seem very interesting üòó Make this combo in the morning and you'll be sure to last until noon üòÅ
üî¥ Tung Da Nang - Sticky Rice with Banh Mi Soup

Today around 7:45 p.m., September 27, I went to buy food. I kept calling. THE PINK SHIRT didn't even look at me. When I ordered, she scowled at me. I told her not to put vegetables in the bread. Then she scowled a second time + MOUTH LIKE WANT TO CURSE you. After about 5 minutes, a male friend, my younger brother, came in to buy it. reviews.author: Linda Yonemoto
reviews.text:
13k for a very delicious bowl of banh canh with fish, a thickened (broth) noodle soup a bit like Japanese udon. There are chopped herbs, fried shallots, some sliced fish cake, and a few pieces of semi dried fish inside. If you want extra side toppings, you can add on a bowl of extra toppings for another 13k. There may also be plain banh mi you can use for dipping for 3k.

If you don't like spicy, kindly let the lady serving you know before she makes you a bowl. Otherwise, she will add chili oil. I liked the chili oil as it provided good balance to the dish, but not everyone eats chile. It packs a good punch along with the peppercorns. There are even more spicy red chiles on the table.

This place is a longstanding restaurant institution catering mainly to locals. Similar to a cafeteria experience, you line up to order and carry the food to your table. They serve hundreds (maybe thousands according to some Google reviewers) of people. We were so happy to go when they opened a little after 2pm. Lots of locals were eating multiple bowls. I can imagine it being incredibly busy during peak hours. Must try dish! So very delicious.  Bring cash!

reviews.text: I came home from eating and was so upset that I had to leave a review, it was so bad, so bad. I went on Wednesday night this week. Next, the mixed rice paper has been mixed for a long time, chewy, and wrapped together. Very little topping. Actually, under Tran Thi Ly bridge, mixed rice paper is even better. I think if a restaurant hires advertising to have people come and review it, then customers should do as advertised. Here in the video, one thing in real life is another, it's like deceiving customers. The only saving grace is a glass of coke that's okay to drink. Run out of. 1.5/5 stars. reviews.author: Ph√∫c Ti·∫øn (Ph√∫c Ti·∫øn Tarot)
reviews.text:
**Dai Bi Quan - Where the Essence of Vegetarian Cuisine Converges in Da Nang**

Dai Bi Quan, located in Da Nang city, is an ideal destination for those who love vegetarian cuisine. With reasonable prices, each dish here costs less than 50,000 VND, but the quality and taste far exceed expectations. The owner, with passion and dedication, has created dishes that are not only delicious but also nutritious, bringing a wonderful culinary experience to diners.

The restaurant space is designed to be cozy and peaceful, creating a feeling of relaxation and peace. This is the ideal place to enjoy a meal in a quiet atmosphere, away from the noise of daily life. In particular, the shop also has a stall selling worship statues and incense lights, serving the spiritual needs of customers.

Dai Bi Quan is not only a restaurant, but also a place where cuisine and spirituality intersect, giving diners memorable experiences. If you are looking for a vegetarian cuisine place in Da Nang, Dai Bi Quan is definitely an option not to be missed.

I was so excited to try this place especially since the reviews raved it! We came in the morning but it was sold out so we came back in the evening.

It was $20,000. Maybe I should have asked for additional meat, or just extra fat pieces? You can see from the pieces, the top pink was the pork skin, the 2nd and 3rd pieces were the fat of the char siu. I was sadly disappointed after reading such high reviews.

reviews.author: Evan Lee
reviews.text:
Da Nang is known for their Mi Quang (Cantonese egg noodles) but there are so many that sells the dish it's hard to distinguish what is good and what is not. Especially when you consider that it is a tourist city and you pay for a mark up as a foreigner, or watered down taste to fit the masses. Mi Quang Ba Dinh is not foreigner friendly, but it is amazingly good. Try to get a table before noon and you'll fight a sea of locals, foodies, and food delivery drivers trying to get a bowl of Mi Quang from here.

Tucked in a small street a few blocks from Cho Con (street market), this is a small family run operation. Their menu is simple and they serve one thing and one thing only. There are no bells and whistles with frog or exotic meats. It's just pork, chicken or shrimp and quail eggs. A small is 25k and a large is 30k. Ultra budget friendly and great family service for extra points. But the real star here is obviously the food. The broth is amazing good. It's rich and semi thick with a little spicy kick built in. No, you can't ask for a non spicy bowl. Man up and eat it like how it's meant to be eaten and see why this spot is a local favorite. If you want to try a Da Nang specialty dish like Mi Quang, this is the place to go.  Don't go to any fancy restaurants and eat where the locals eat. You won't be disappointed!

reviews.text:
We drove past Ngu Hanh Son, the distance to the store was a bit far but the quality was worth the effort. The newly opened restaurant is the second location of the grilled chicken feet restaurant that I often eat at.

About space and people:
The shop is beautifully designed, the space is airy and spacious. Friendly and cute staff. There was a helmet for us to get in so we wouldn't get wet (this small action is a plus point for the service)

About food:

I quite like the vermicelli noodle dish, the sauce is medium sweet, very Northern.
The shrimp paste is fragrant, probably cooked by distillation so it doesn't feel dark, quite suitable to eat with vermicelli and tofu.
Chicken feet with Thai sauce is the most delicious dish I have ever enjoyed in Da Nang, chewy, crispy, fresh and rich.

The food price is also reasonable and reasonable, I find it cheap.

If I can comment, I hope next time there will be a little more music, because music also contributes to the emotions of foodüåª

Will support this shop for a long time. Thank you shop and staff

reviews.text:
üè† The shop is located on the front of Y Lan Nguyen Phi street. The space of the restaurant is simple, except for paintings on the walls, there is no other decoration. The restaurant only has indoor seating (no air conditioning). The shop uses low tables and chairs, chairs with backrests, tables are a bit small, so if there are more than 4 people, you have to combine tables together. The restaurant has small trash cans at each table.

üåØ The main dish of the shop is Nem Nuong, sold by the box, customers roll it themselves to eat. There are also Bun Nem Nuong, Shrimp Cakes, Grilled Meat Skewers, Stuffed Snails and a few other snacks, the menu is also quite diverse. I tried the Nem Nuong, in general it was to my taste, the dipping sauce was also quite delicious (the dipping sauce was a bit thick at first, but if you add more sweet fish sauce, it will taste better).

üí∞ The restaurant has a menu with clear prices, illustrations of dishes, and¬† eat first and pay later. A large portion of Nem Nuong costs 55k, enough for one person to eat. Reasonable price range compared to the quality of the food.

üåü The restaurant is suitable for individual dining or groups of 02 or more people. The shop is not suitable for sitting for long periods of time because the low tables and chairs can easily tire your legs.

üïõ This review was written after visiting the restaurant on November 27, 2023.

reviews.author: Victoria P.
reviews.text: This is one of THE BEST bun bo we‚Äôve had in Vietnam. It‚Äôs very similar to the bun bo in Saigon which I absolutely love. Drinks were cheap and huge! We saw a family of diners that seemed like regulars, and the restaurant owner was playing with their child as soon as he had a moment, so adorable! He was also very appreciative when we said that it was the best bun bo in town. All the floor staff were so hardworking and polite as well. Highly recommended!!

reviews.text:
The shop is small but has both space and curbside. I ordered self-rolls for 45k with toppings of boiled eggs, spring rolls, spring rolls, grilled spring rolls, grilled meat, banh hoi, raw vegetables, sliced ‚Äã‚Äãmango and crispy cake. It was ok but the crispy cake was a bit hard and a little oily, the dipping sauce was greasy. You can eat peanut sauce or sweet chili sauce (available on the table, just mix it yourself to suit your taste), servings of 1-2 people. If you don't like to roll it yourself, you can order it pre-rolled. Grilled pork noodle soup 25k has a lot of meat and can be eaten with sweet chili sauce or peanut sauce, but it's okay to eat, not very special.
In short, a dish you should try to know Binh Dinh cuisine. It's ok to eat for fun once in a while, and the price is also ok and suitable for everyone.
You can try Nha Trang's grilled spring rolls, which are quite delicious, also rolled like this but with a different sauce, on Huynh Thuc Khang street.

The food was fine but the staff was very rude to us. When my cousin and I sat down and talked in English (I am Vietnamese but live in Germany, my cousin is Vietnamese), the staff was looking at us. Then while eating, a man (probably the owner?) asked us where we come from. We told him I was Vietnamese but from Germany and she was Vietnamese. Few minutes later more customers came into the restaurant and the man started speaking English to them, even though they were vietnamese. He started talking to other customers in English too who came before us. We heard that the customers were obviously all Vietnamese..
He was making fun of us by suddenly speaking English eventhough we were Vietnamese nationality. My Vietnamese is broken, so it was more comfortable for me to speak English. He disrespected us in such a bad, rude and disrespectful way..

Will never eat here again. This is racism that I am not going to take. We will go elsewhere for B√°nh Tr√°ng N∆∞·ªõng but not here anymore.

reviews.author: ƒê·∫∑ng T√¥
reviews.text:
If my friend hadn't invited me here, I probably would never have experienced the drinks here. I passed by many times and saw that the restaurant was big and luxurious, but I wasn't very attracted to this type of drink.
The menu here has a variety of prices from 29k - 59k. I ordered 4 drinks:
- Oriental coconut milk: 10/10, I want to drink this again, the taste is very familiar but overall delicious.
- Quan Am lemon tea: not as sour as I expected, drinkable, strong tea 7/10
- Yakult grape green tea: this is delicious but if you don't ask for a little sugar, it will be very sweet. It has small white pearls the size of semolina grains when they expand, chewing the mouthful 9/10
- Grape Jello Tea: My friend told me to have this without sugar so it's a bit astringent, but it's probably delicious with sugar. 8/10
- Jumbo fruit tea: 10/10, buy more white pearls to make it more delicious, rich in flavor, 2 people drink 1 cup of this because it's a lot.
The space here is spacious and beautiful, but on the upper floor you can't see much out, so for some people it will feel a bit cramped.
Minus point: drinks in tall glasses, like me carrying 4 glasses, are quite heavy. If the customer can't balance it on a tray, the glass will tilt and fall, so the tray should be designed with a hole to fit the glass in securely. .
The toilet floor is not clean, the curtain blocking the way to the toilet is dirty.

reviews.author: Emmi Pham
reviews.text:
Ambiance
Kitachi offers a cozy, Korean-inspired space with warm, subtle tones. It‚Äôs spacious and well-ventilated, featuring floor seating that adds to the casual, relaxed vibe, making it perfect for gatherings with friends or family.

Food Quality
Kitachi‚Äôs spicy noodles are flavorful, with chewy noodles and a rich, authentically spicy broth. Customers can choose their preferred spice level, from mild to extremely hot. Besides spicy noodles, the menu includes other popular Korean dishes such as tteokbokki, Korean-style fried chicken, and bibimbap, offering plenty of options for diners.

Pricing
Prices at Kitachi are reasonable for the quality and service. The spicy noodle dishes are affordably priced, making it accessible for students and anyone looking for an enjoyable Korean dining experience.

Service
The staff at Kitachi are friendly, attentive, and quick. Even when the restaurant is busy, dishes are served promptly, so there‚Äôs little waiting time.

Conclusion
Kitachi is a great spot to enjoy authentic Korean flavors in the heart of Da Nang. With its comfortable atmosphere, tasty dishes, and fair pricing, it‚Äôs a must-try for fans of Korean cuisine, especially those craving spicy noodles.

I bought broken rice to take away with a fried egg and grilled pork chop for VND 50.000, with an extra VND 5.000 for extra rice. The restaurant serves quickly, and the advantage is that the rice is put in an aluminium foil tray.

As for the taste of the dish, I was disappointed with the grilled pork chop. It did not taste like the Saigon-style grilled pork chop that I am used to. I do not understand why the restaurant would keep adjusting the seasoning and labeling it as Saigon when the taste of the dish is not the same as the original place.

Compared to the price, I find it not worth it. Overall, I would not recommend this restaurant for broken rice. There are much better options available in Da Nang.

reviews.author: Trang Thuy Dieu Thuy
reviews.text: The milk tea tastes like it's old, has been left for a long time, no longer has the taste and smell of tea. The attitude and way of talking of Quan Yin points ü•π. Customers report that the milk tea is sour and does not have a tea aroma, the shop responds that the shop tastes normal, There's nothing wrong with it, if the shop tastes sour then the shop will fix it ü§£, and they say it's because the white tapioca pearls are sour??? After that, there was a customer who called the customer later to ask if the tea was normal??? Does the product sent to each customer have to be the same? From purchasing ingredients, preserving, mixing, packaging, and delivering, there are so many steps? How can a restaurant be so sure that they make every glass exactly the same and call customers later to check? Why don't you think about the case where the employee made a mistake in this application, or used the items from the previous day and insisted that the restaurant was right and the customer was wrong??? Is it true that when the restaurant tastes bth, the customer has to accept that it is not sour? I've ordered from the restaurant a few times, but this time there was a problem, so I just responded. I see that the restaurant is really irresponsible. The photo looks ok, but I can only eat the toppings and leave the milk tea alone.

reviews.author: Truong Nhu Quynh
reviews.text: Commenting on the taste of the drinks at the restaurant, the owner said it was normal. Can I ask if there is a flavor of custard tea or milk tea that is salty and brackish? If I say it alone, it may not be right, but many people have reported that this shop definitely has problems. The same goes for the cheese topping. Disgusting, the first time I ate it I felt nauseous. I ordered 8 portions, all 8 people left almost half a glass unfinished. Maybe if I had this glass, I would hold my breath and drink most of the water but leave the topping behind because I couldn't use it. If I ate it, I would probably vomit it all. The feedback is like the shop owner is "unsatisfied" with the customer's "critical" comments. The price is more expensive than the average price and the water is disgusting. My comments are based on my experience, so please don't make the same mistake. Thanks!

I'm okay with the attitude, then I saw bth so I didn't return the money, I said I don't need it, I just went to google to rate it a bit and suddenly realized I wasn't alone.

reviews.text: We ate fried chicken and 4 cheese pizza. Fried chikcen is korean style but menu shows a normal fried chicken. reviews.author: Niklas Johansson
reviews.text:
If you're looking for international dishes, the best pizza or burger in this part of town, go here!! They are fantastic! They also serve the best morning glory ever and have many Vietnamese options. My strongest recommendations!

The family running the business is super friendly! The street is very quiet.

The pizza bottoms are stiff but not too hard. The crust is awesome. The ratio of cheese and topping is great. Of the burgers I had the bacon cheese which was beautifully served. Unlike most burgers, this one did not fall apart from taking good size bites.

Both my visits late in the evening and afternoon I've been a lone customer and had a chance to speak with the family. They're friendly and speak some English. I had a very good time, learnt some more Vietnamese and got some local recommendations.

I'll be back many times.

reviews.author: jason lee
reviews.text:
Amazing food and experience. I rarely even bother to give even bad reviews, much less good reviews. But to anyone who sees this, this place is a must-try. I ordered this 2 dishes that  you see above, 1 was the seafood pizza and the other I believe is called banh xeo. The food tasted amazing. Location wise, this place is definitely obscure and hard to find, but the quality wise is definitely worth the effort to find the place.

Over the past few days in vietnam had a few scam experiences (1 kept pushing me to order and even pretended he sold char siew but ended up serving roast pork which was exorbitently priced). My whole experience at vietnam was almost ruined but finding this place changed my impression.

Probs up to the Boss and the lady boss for the great food and customer experience. Will definitely visit this place again in my next trip.

reviews.author: Reginald Williams
reviews.text:
My coffee pour over Vietnamese coffee was certainly tasty. The chairs were reasonably comfortable. But otherwise, the experience here was pretty generic.  The ambience has little
Charisma and the baristas seem to have little interest in doing more than filling orders, and little patience for questions nor for indecisive customers. Layout of the shop is very boring though the floor to ceiling windows provide a cheerful note to liven up an otherwise uninteresting interior.  Sadly, drinks are significantly pricier than other places offering the same quality but better atmosphere. Turns out the business participated in a Korean network that offers a significant discount to customers who join the network and agree to review the places they visit. You would only know this of you read Korean, however, and so the discount is not a available to others. Seems their high prices are subsidizing these customers.

reviews.author: Genevieve Vox
reviews.text:
If you are planning a visit to this eatery, be mindful of peak hours. Expect a bustling atmosphere with people eagerly awaiting their meals. While the owner and his wife work tirelessly to keep up with the demand, the limited staff can struggle with a large influx of customers. While the wait for food might be lengthy, the reward is undeniably delicious.

The fried rice stands out with its smoky aroma from the wok, boasting perfectly cooked grains with minimal to no grease. Each portion is generously sized, ensuring you leave satisfied. The braise beef, however, could benefit from a more vibrant colour and a thicker consistency. A touch more seasoning would also elevate the dish. For those who enjoy a kick, having chilli salt on hand would be a welcome addition for dipping the beef.

B√∫n B√≤ B√† R∆°i proudly displays its Michelin Award at the entrance, and I can see why. The restaurant is simply set up, but that‚Äôs part of the charm of many Vietnamese places. The service was incredibly friendly. Even though their English wasn‚Äôt perfect, I felt warmly welcomed, and they immediately introduced me to their best-selling dish.

I also appreciated the little guide on how to properly enjoy the meal. The dish itself was absolutely delicious. The broth was rich and flavorful, with a variety of meats, each one incredibly tender and packed with taste. I would have loved to order a second portion, but I was more than satisfied after finishing.

Every time I go to buy rice, there's this girl standing at the counter who talks in a very polite way. But I still let it go and often buy rice because it's close to home and the rice is quite suitable for my taste and the turmeric vermicelli sold in the afternoon is delicious. Today when I went to the restaurant to buy rice as usual, when I went to point at the mirror to choose the dish (I knocked very lightly), she said, "Don't knock on the mirror, it will make the mirror angry" with a VERY ATTITUDE tone! If you're afraid of breaking the mirror or feel uncomfortable, I think you should say something like a reminder or something. Because after all, I spend money to buy food, not to ask for food from a restaurant. And I silently walked to the car so my friend could buy it. But while she was doing it for my friend, she turned into an attitude and shouted loudly at the people in the shop and my friend told me to bring it back for help but she ignored it. And my friend couldn't stand her attitude in the middle of a hot afternoon, so we decided not to buy it anymore! I think the shop should give you some feedback.

reviews.author: Tu Ho
reviews.text:
The first time I ate, I ordered stuffed squid rice + stir-fried tripe with turmeric. The price is 35k, I think the price is okay, not cheap but not expensive
The second time I ate, I ordered stuffed squid rice + shrimp (exactly 2 as shown in the picture). Because it was my second meal, I didn't ask the price. When the staff brought it out, they gave me an additional card with the number 55 (you can see in the picture), and I realized that my portion cost 55k. I had a question with an employee: "Why did the last meal cost 35k, but this time eating shrimp is only a little more expensive?". That friend replied, "Squid rice is already 40k." I asked again, "So these 2 small shrimps cost 15k?". The staff was silent and didn't answer, then left, not caring anymore, like your dad doesn't like to answer anymore.
I had to stay silent, very angry but still tried to eat it all and then payed to go home.
I will never come back to this restaurant again, it's so bad in terms of prices and staff attitude.
Please be careful when coming to this restaurant. When choosing a dish, always ask how much it costs, to avoid being ripped off like me.

reviews.text: Apparently, the two of us went to eat. PART 8 CHICKEN 1 NOODLE. Please order your own noodles." I was very upset so I said I didn't need it anymore, but my friend knew I wanted to eat noodles so he ordered more. Obviously the operator made a mistake but neither took responsibility nor apologized to the customer, blaming the customer. If you order for a customer, please pay attention to what the customer is saying, but if the customer points directly at the menu 2 or 3 times, and the wrong order is given to the customer, I don't understand what you are standing there for. That's what the customer asked for. When resolved, the attitude is unpleasant. Going out to eat makes you angry. If the nvien apologizes to the customer for the wrong order and hopes the customer will sympathize, then as a customer I won't rate anything. reviews.author: All Things Oahu
reviews.text:
We have always known of the more popular place and usually go there but wanted to venture out to something different and give another restaurant a chance.

They did not disappoint!

I guess the other place may have better advertising but I promise you this place is good too AND a little cheaper! What can go wrong, and I have to be honest, the sauce here is even BETTER tasting than the other place!

We weren't sure what to expect and since there was no one in the restaurant we were a little hesitant BUT based on the 4.4 out of 5 reviews, we thought why not!

I loved the decor! It is another place in time for H·ªèi An so I'm certain this is where they owners are from! I loved the painting of the Japanese Bridge and the farmlands as well as the beautiful straw hats.

The older gentleman and his wife were very sweet and kind! The son made our crepes.  I am even going as far as saying that I truly believe the Nem L·ª•i (ground meat skewers taste better than tue other place!

Overall, we will definitely come back here! Their Grilled Meat Skewers looked so good that we had to order some to go to taste!  Since they made the ground meat taste better than tue other place, surely their grilled meat will be just as wonderful!

The meat was just right, the smokiness and sweet, salty and lemongrass was all just perfect!  The flavors were just wonderful - perfect blend of flavors! I guess it love it because it is how they make it in the south!

Highly recommended this place!

Give them a shot! Go out of the norm and help out a smaller shop that has food just as amazing - if not more amazing than the other place!

We liked it so much we ordered another round of Banh Xeo, Nem L·ª•i, Th·ªãt N∆∞·ªõng and B√∫n Th·ªãt N∆∞·ªõng for dinner tonight!

Please help out a smaller shop and I promise you won't be disappointed! I can't believe it took me this long to try out a new place!

5 out of 5 for sure!

PS I also wanted to respond to@Kelsey's 2 star review saying she spent over $20 USD for food she didn't order - it's Asia! Don't eat it and you won't get charged...

My husband and ordered Banh Xeo, Nem L·ª•i, and 2 drinks at the restaurant and then we ordered another Banh Xeo, Nem L·ª•i, and added 2 additional Bun Thit Nuong plates along with another side order of the Thit Nuong to go, and all of that came to 490,000 vnƒë. $19.11 total - nothing like the supposed amount she gave! What a sad excuse of lies...I even took a photo at home to prove it. Basically we will have almost 3 meals from this so I have no idea why Kelly was so mean spirited to try to lie like that.

Also @Bryan - every single restaurant charges for those napkins. It's no secret.

reviews.author: Giulia Matelli
reviews.text: Hatsim might be my favourite discovery while I was in Danang! I had it 3 days in a row and each time was amazing, I tried different types of drinks. The ladies at the cafe were nice and hospitable, and it has outdoor seating on a pretty street. The salted cream was so delicious, and I really liked the puffed cake they have to go with a drink. So rare to find fully vegan drinks places, I can‚Äôt wait to come back!

reviews.author: Erik Marcus
reviews.text:
I've eaten at vegan restaurants in dozens of countries, but have never found a place like Hatsim, which serves several dozen varities of drinks based on nut milk, coffee, tea, and juice. I've sampled most of the menu and while it's all delicious the standouts are the iced cashew milk salted cream coffee and the weird-sounding-but-totally delicious pineapple leaf cashew green bean milk (with black tapioca cubes!). All their drinks are non-dairy and vegan. When ordering coffee or tea-based drinks, you can have them omit the sugar although the nutmilk mixers are pre-sweetened.

The restaurant is owned by a twenty-something Vietnamese couple, both of whom speak pretty good English and are SO nice. They've got little chairs and tables in front if you want to sit down, or you can order to go. If you get your order to stay, you can request it in a glass rather than a plastic cup. No doubt because of the quality of their offerings, they do loads of business‚Äîmostly from Grab delivery. Super cheap and super healthy. I spent a few weeks living up the street and I found myself here at least twice a day.

reviews.author: Genevieve Vox
reviews.text:
If you are in the mood for a taste of Thailand without leaving the comfort of your couch, look no further than Pi Thai. I recently placed an order through a food delivery app. Their array of tempting promotions and discount codes made my bowl of pork noodle soup a steal at only VND 25.000.

The noodles themselves were a highlight, perfectly chewy with a satisfying bite. Some might find them undercooked, but I absolutely loved their springy texture.

I opted for a clear broth that was subtly sweet, with the perfect balance waiting to be enhanced by a drizzle of their prik nam som sauce. This vibrant condiment added a tangy, citrusy kick that took the soup to another level. Ô∏è

The suki sauce for dipping the pork was another winner, sweet and savoury with a hint of umami, it was the ideal partner for the tender slices of meat.

No Thai meal is complete without a classic Thai red milk tea. Pi Thai's version hit all the right notes ‚Äì fragrant, creamy, and perfectly sweet, it was the perfect way to wash down the savoury flavours.
